@startuml operator-rbac-reach
' Where the operator ServiceAccount can reach, split by the same three grant families as the gateway.
' Source of truth: docs/src/security/rbac.md
!include _style.puml

skinparam wrapWidth 350
skinparam nodesep 18
skinparam ranksep 34
skinparam rectangle {
  roundCorner 4
}

rectangle "**Operator ServiceAccount**\nagentry-system/agentry-controller" as OPSA #back:87CEEB;line:0D47A1;line.bold;text:0a2540

' ---------- family 1: ClusterRole ----------
rectangle "**reach: every namespace in the cluster**\na ClusterRoleBinding cannot be namespace-limited" as band #line:B71C1C;line.dashed;text:B71C1C {
  rectangle "**Agentry CRDs**\nAgent, AgentTask, AgentChannel,\nModelProvider, AgentClass\n**get, list, watch, create,**\n**update, patch, delete**\n....\n***/status**  **update, patch**\nseparate grants: with the status\nsubresource enabled, write on the main\nresource does **not** permit status writes\n....\n***/finalizers**  **update**\nreconcilers set ownerRefs with\nblockOwnerDeletion: true, and the\nOwnerReferencesPermissionEnforcement\nadmission plugin authorizes that against\nthe owner's finalizers subresource" as crds #back:F5F5F5;line:9E9E9E;line.bold;text:2a0a4a

  rectangle "**Pods**, **PersistentVolumeClaims**,\n**Services**, **ConfigMaps**,\n**NetworkPolicies**, **ServiceAccounts**\n**get, list, watch, create,**\n**update, patch, delete**\nNetworkPolicy and ServiceAccount are\nsynthesized per Agent / per AgentTask and\nowner-referenced for cascade GC, so create\nand delete must reach user namespaces.\nlist and watch feed controller-runtime's\ninformers. Pods is cluster-wide also because\nthe AgentReconciler enumerates gateway\nPods in agentry-system for the activity fan-out." as core #back:F5F5F5;line:9E9E9E;line.bold;text:2a0a4a

  rectangle "**cert-manager.io/v1 Certificate**\n**get, list, watch, create,**\n**update, patch, delete**\nthe per-Agent and per-AgentTask certs live\nalongside the workload, not agentry-system.\nlist and watch are required so the reconciler\ncan observe status.conditions[type=Ready]\nbefore creating the dependent Pod." as certs #back:F5F5F5;line:9E9E9E;line.bold;text:2a0a4a

  rectangle "**roles**, **rolebindings**\n(rbac.authorization.k8s.io)\n**get, list, watch, create, update, delete**\n**+ escalate**   **+ bind**\nboth verbs are load-bearing: see the legend" as rbacres #back:F5F5F5;line:B71C1C;line.bold;text:2a0a4a

  rectangle "**RuntimeClass**, **StorageClass**, **Namespaces**\n**get, list, watch** (validation)\n....\n**Events**  **create, patch**" as meta #back:F5F5F5;line:9E9E9E;line.bold;text:2a0a4a

  rectangle "**ciliumnetworkpolicies.cilium.io**\nor the Calico Enterprise equivalent\n//conditional: the chart templates these//\n//rules only when FQDN egress synthesis is//\n//switched on (allowedHosts on a supported//\n//CNI). A cluster without it never grants them.//" as cni #back:F5F5F5;line:9E9E9E;line.dashed;text:757575
}

' ---------- family 2: namespaced Role ----------
rectangle "namespace: **agentry-system**" as nssys #line:0D47A1;line.dashed;text:0a2540 {
  rectangle "**Leases**\n**get, list, watch, create,**\n**update, patch, delete**\ncontroller-runtime's leader-election lock\nneeds the full set. Shipping it as the\nnamespaced Role is what actually\nconfines it to agentry-system." as leases #back:FFD580;line:7a3f00;line.bold;text:3a1f00
  rectangle "**Secrets**\n**get, list, watch**\nagentry-system **only**, never cluster-wide.\nValidates that ModelProvider credential\nSecrets exist and are well-formed." as secs #back:FFD580;line:7a3f00;line.bold;text:3a1f00
}

' ---------- family 3: dynamic per-namespace Roles ----------
rectangle "a user namespace, per AgentChannel" as nsuser #line:7a3f00;line.dashed;text:3a1f00 {
  rectangle "channel **Secret(s)**\n**get, watch**\nresourceNames-scoped to the Secret(s) named\nby that AgentChannel's webhook auth config.\n//list omitted//: resourceNames cannot\nconstrain it. A name-scoped watch must set\nfieldSelector metadata.name=<secret>.\n....\nUsed **only** by the AgentChannelReconciler, to\ncheck that the configured **data** key is present.\nTorn down with the AgentChannel." as chsec #back:FFD580;line:7a3f00;line.bold;text:3a1f00
}

' ---------- the three edge classes ----------
OPSA -[#B71C1C,bold]-> crds : **ClusterRole**\n+ ClusterRoleBinding
OPSA -[#B71C1C,bold]-> core
OPSA -[#B71C1C,bold]-> certs
OPSA -[#B71C1C,bold]-> rbacres
OPSA -[#B71C1C,bold]-> meta
OPSA .[#9E9E9E,bold].> cni : conditional
OPSA -[#0D47A1]-> leases : **Role** + RoleBinding\nin agentry-system
OPSA -[#0D47A1]-> secs
OPSA .[#7a3f00,bold].> chsec : **dynamic Role**\nper AgentChannel

crds -[hidden]down- core
core -[hidden]down- certs
certs -[hidden]down- rbacres
rbacres -[hidden]down- meta
meta -[hidden]down- cni
leases -[hidden]down- secs

legend bottom
  **The same three edge classes as the gateway, and the same ClusterRole/Role split**, for the same reason: a
  ClusterRoleBinding applies in every namespace, so anything that must be namespace-limited (Leases, Secrets)
  has to ship as a separate namespaced Role. **The operator does not hold cluster-wide Secret access.** Unlike a
  sidecar model, credentials stay with the gateway in agentry-system and are never copied to user namespaces.
  ====
  **Why escalate AND bind.** Kubernetes escalation prevention forbids creating a Role that grants permissions the
  creator does not itself hold, and the per-channel Roles grant user-namespace Secret reads the operator
  deliberately lacks as a standing permission. **escalate** satisfies that check when creating or updating the Role.
  **bind** is separately required for the RoleBinding half: Kubernetes permits creating a RoleBinding referencing a
  Role only if the creator either holds everything the Role grants, or holds bind on it. One verb does not cover both.
  ====
  **This is a deliberate trade, and the operator ServiceAccount should be audited as privileged.** The alternative that
  satisfies the escalation check without escalate is granting the operator standing Secret read across all user
  namespaces, which is strictly worse: it turns a create-time capability into an always-on read surface.
endlegend
@enduml
